2202 template<typename T>
2203 static LanguageLinkage getDeclLanguageLinkage(const T &D) {
2204  // C++ [dcl.link]p1: All function types, function names with external linkage,
2205  // and variable names with external linkage have a language linkage.
2206  if (!D.hasExternalFormalLinkage())
2207  return NoLanguageLinkage;
2208 
2209  // Language linkage is a C++ concept, but saying that everything else in C has
2210  // C language linkage fits the implementation nicely.
2211  if (!D.getASTContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
2212  return CLanguageLinkage;
2213 
2214  // C++ [dcl.link]p4: A C language linkage is ignored in determining the
2215  // language linkage of the names of class members and the function type of
2216  // class member functions.
2217  const DeclContext *DC = D.getDeclContext();
2218  if (DC->isRecord())
2219  return CXXLanguageLinkage;
2220 
2221  // If the first decl is in an extern "C" context, any other redeclaration
2222  // will have C language linkage. If the first one is not in an extern "C"
2223  // context, we would have reported an error for any other decl being in one.
2224  if (isFirstInExternCContext(&D))
2225  return CLanguageLinkage;
2226  return CXXLanguageLinkage;
2227 }
2228 
2229 template<typename T>
2230 static bool isDeclExternC(const T &D) {
2231  // Since the context is ignored for class members, they can only have C++
2232  // language linkage or no language linkage.
2233  const DeclContext *DC = D.getDeclContext();
2234  if (DC->isRecord()) {
2235  assert(D.getASTContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus);
2236  return false;
2237  }
2238 
2239  return D.getLanguageLinkage() == CLanguageLinkage;
2240 }
2241 
2242 LanguageLinkage VarDecl::getLanguageLinkage() const {
2243  return getDeclLanguageLinkage(*this);
2244 }
2245 
2246 bool VarDecl::isExternC() const {
2247  return isDeclExternC(*this);
2248 }

2258 VarDecl *VarDecl::getCanonicalDecl() { return getFirstDecl(); }
2259 
2260 VarDecl::DefinitionKind
2261 VarDecl::isThisDeclarationADefinition(ASTContext &C) const {
2262  if (isThisDeclarationADemotedDefinition())
2263  return DeclarationOnly;
2264 
2265  // C++ [basic.def]p2:
2266  // A declaration is a definition unless [...] it contains the 'extern'
2267  // specifier or a linkage-specification and neither an initializer [...],
2268  // it declares a non-inline static data member in a class declaration [...],
2269  // it declares a static data member outside a class definition and the variable
2270  // was defined within the class with the constexpr specifier [...],
2271  // C++1y [temp.expl.spec]p15:
2272  // An explicit specialization of a static data member or an explicit
2273  // specialization of a static data member template is a definition if the
2274  // declaration includes an initializer; otherwise, it is a declaration.
2275  //
2276  // FIXME: How do you declare (but not define) a partial specialization of
2277  // a static data member template outside the containing class?
2278  if (isStaticDataMember()) {
2279  if (isOutOfLine() &&
2280  !(getCanonicalDecl()->isInline() &&
2281  getCanonicalDecl()->isConstexpr()) &&
2282  (hasInit() ||
2283  // If the first declaration is out-of-line, this may be an
2284  // instantiation of an out-of-line partial specialization of a variable
2285  // template for which we have not yet instantiated the initializer.
2286  (getFirstDecl()->isOutOfLine()
2287  ? getTemplateSpecializationKind() == TSK_Undeclared
2288  : getTemplateSpecializationKind() !=
2289  TSK_ExplicitSpecialization) ||
2290  isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(this)))
2291  return Definition;
2292  if (!isOutOfLine() && isInline())
2293  return Definition;
2294  return DeclarationOnly;
2295  }
2296  // C99 6.7p5:
2297  // A definition of an identifier is a declaration for that identifier that
2298  // [...] causes storage to be reserved for that object.
2299  // Note: that applies for all non-file-scope objects.
2300  // C99 6.9.2p1:
2301  // If the declaration of an identifier for an object has file scope and an
2302  // initializer, the declaration is an external definition for the identifier
2303  if (hasInit())
2304  return Definition;
2305 
2306  if (hasDefiningAttr())
2307  return Definition;
2308 
2309  if (const auto *SAA = getAttr<SelectAnyAttr>())
2310  if (!SAA->isInherited())
2311  return Definition;
2312 
2313  // A variable template specialization (other than a static data member
2314  // template or an explicit specialization) is a declaration until we
2315  // instantiate its initializer.
2316  if (auto *VTSD = dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(this)) {
2317  if (VTSD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() != TSK_ExplicitSpecialization &&
2318  !isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(VTSD) &&
2319  !VTSD->IsCompleteDefinition)
2320  return DeclarationOnly;
2321  }
2322 
2323  if (hasExternalStorage())
2324  return DeclarationOnly;
2325 
2326  // [dcl.link] p7:
2327  // A declaration directly contained in a linkage-specification is treated
2328  // as if it contains the extern specifier for the purpose of determining
2329  // the linkage of the declared name and whether it is a definition.
2330  if (isSingleLineLanguageLinkage(*this))
2331  return DeclarationOnly;
2332 
2333  // C99 6.9.2p2:
2334  // A declaration of an object that has file scope without an initializer,
2335  // and without a storage class specifier or the scs 'static', constitutes
2336  // a tentative definition.
2337  // No such thing in C++.
2338  if (!C.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && isFileVarDecl())
2339  return TentativeDefinition;
2340 
2341  // What's left is (in C, block-scope) declarations without initializers or
2342  // external storage. These are definitions.
2343  return Definition;
2344 }
2345 
2346 VarDecl *VarDecl::getActingDefinition() {
2347  DefinitionKind Kind = isThisDeclarationADefinition();
2348  if (Kind != TentativeDefinition)
2349  return nullptr;
2350 
2351  VarDecl *LastTentative = nullptr;
2352 
2353  // Loop through the declaration chain, starting with the most recent.
2354  for (VarDecl *Decl = getMostRecentDecl(); Decl;
2355  Decl = Decl->getPreviousDecl()) {
2356  Kind = Decl->isThisDeclarationADefinition();
2357  if (Kind == Definition)
2358  return nullptr;
2359  // Record the first (most recent) TentativeDefinition that is encountered.
2360  if (Kind == TentativeDefinition && !LastTentative)
2361  LastTentative = Decl;
2362  }
2363 
2364  return LastTentative;
2365 }
2366 
2367 VarDecl *VarDecl::getDefinition(ASTContext &C) {
2368  VarDecl *First = getFirstDecl();
2369  for (auto *I : First->redecls()) {
2370  if (I->isThisDeclarationADefinition(C) == Definition)
2371  return I;
2372  }
2373  return nullptr;
2374 }
2375 
2376 VarDecl::DefinitionKind VarDecl::hasDefinition(ASTContext &C) const {
2377  DefinitionKind Kind = DeclarationOnly;
2378 
2379  const VarDecl *First = getFirstDecl();
2380  for (auto *I : First->redecls()) {
2381  Kind = std::max(Kind, I->isThisDeclarationADefinition(C));
2382  if (Kind == Definition)
2383  break;
2384  }
2385 
2386  return Kind;
2387 }

2430  if (I->hasInit())

2442 bool VarDecl::isOutOfLine() const {
2443  if (Decl::isOutOfLine())
2444  return true;
2445 
2446  if (!isStaticDataMember())
2447  return false;
2448 
2449  // If this static data member was instantiated from a static data member of
2450  // a class template, check whether that static data member was defined
2451  // out-of-line.
2452  if (VarDecl *VD = getInstantiatedFromStaticDataMember())
2453  return VD->isOutOfLine();

2455  return false;

2466 
2467 bool VarDecl::mightBeUsableInConstantExpressions(const ASTContext &C) const {
2468  const LangOptions &Lang = C.getLangOpts();
2469 
2470  // OpenCL permits const integral variables to be used in constant
2471  // expressions, like in C++98.
2472  if (!Lang.CPlusPlus && !Lang.OpenCL && !Lang.C23)
2473  return false;
2474 
2475  // Function parameters are never usable in constant expressions.
2476  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(this))
2477  return false;
2478 
2479  // The values of weak variables are never usable in constant expressions.
2480  if (isWeak())
2481  return false;
2482 
2483  // In C++11, any variable of reference type can be used in a constant
2484  // expression if it is initialized by a constant expression.
2485  if (Lang.CPlusPlus11 && getType()->isReferenceType())
2486  return true;
2487 
2488  // Only const objects can be used in constant expressions in C++. C++98 does
2489  // not require the variable to be non-volatile, but we consider this to be a
2490  // defect.
2491  if (!getType().isConstant(C) || getType().isVolatileQualified())
2492  return false;
2493 
2494  // In C++, but not in C, const, non-volatile variables of integral or
2495  // enumeration types can be used in constant expressions.
2496  if (getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() && !Lang.C23)
2497  return true;
2498 
2499  // C23 6.6p7: An identifier that is:
2500  // ...
2501  // - declared with storage-class specifier constexpr and has an object type,
2502  // is a named constant, ... such a named constant is a constant expression
2503  // with the type and value of the declared object.
2504  // Additionally, in C++11, non-volatile constexpr variables can be used in
2505  // constant expressions.
2506  return (Lang.CPlusPlus11 || Lang.C23) && isConstexpr();
2507 }
2508 
2509 bool VarDecl::isUsableInConstantExpressions(const ASTContext &Context) const {
2510  // C++2a [expr.const]p3:
2511  // A variable is usable in constant expressions after its initializing
2512  // declaration is encountered...
2513  const VarDecl *DefVD = nullptr;
2514  const Expr *Init = getAnyInitializer(DefVD);
2515  if (!Init || Init->isValueDependent() || getType()->isDependentType())
2516  return false;
2517  // ... if it is a constexpr variable, or it is of reference type or of
2518  // const-qualified integral or enumeration type, ...
2519  if (!DefVD->mightBeUsableInConstantExpressions(Context))
2520  return false;
2521  // ... and its initializer is a constant initializer.
2522  if (Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && !DefVD->hasConstantInitialization())
2523  return false;
2524  // C++98 [expr.const]p1:
2525  // An integral constant-expression can involve only [...] const variables
2526  // or static data members of integral or enumeration types initialized with
2527  // [integer] constant expressions (dcl.init)
2528  if ((Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus || Context.getLangOpts().OpenCL) &&
2529  !Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && !DefVD->hasICEInitializer(Context))
2530  return false;
2531  return true;
2532 }
2533 
2534 /// Convert the initializer for this declaration to the elaborated EvaluatedStmt
2535 /// form, which contains extra information on the evaluated value of the
2536 /// initializer.
2537 EvaluatedStmt *VarDecl::ensureEvaluatedStmt() const {
2538  auto *Eval = Init.dyn_cast<EvaluatedStmt *>();
2539  if (!Eval) {
2540  // Note: EvaluatedStmt contains an APValue, which usually holds
2541  // resources not allocated from the ASTContext. We need to do some
2542  // work to avoid leaking those, but we do so in VarDecl::evaluateValue
2543  // where we can detect whether there's anything to clean up or not.
2544  Eval = new (getASTContext()) EvaluatedStmt;
2545  Eval->Value = Init.get<Stmt *>();
2546  Init = Eval;
2547  }
2548  return Eval;
2549 }
2550 
2551 EvaluatedStmt *VarDecl::getEvaluatedStmt() const {
2552  return Init.dyn_cast<EvaluatedStmt *>();
2553 }
2554 
2555 APValue *VarDecl::evaluateValue() const {
2556  SmallVector<PartialDiagnosticAt, 8> Notes;
2557  return evaluateValueImpl(Notes, hasConstantInitialization());
2558 }
2559 
2560 APValue *VarDecl::evaluateValueImpl(SmallVectorImpl<PartialDiagnosticAt> &Notes,
2561  bool IsConstantInitialization) const {
2562  EvaluatedStmt *Eval = ensureEvaluatedStmt();
2563 
2564  const auto *Init = getInit();
2565  assert(!Init->isValueDependent());
2566 
2567  // We only produce notes indicating why an initializer is non-constant the
2568  // first time it is evaluated. FIXME: The notes won't always be emitted the
2569  // first time we try evaluation, so might not be produced at all.
2570  if (Eval->WasEvaluated)
2571  return Eval->Evaluated.isAbsent() ? nullptr : &Eval->Evaluated;
2572 
2573  if (Eval->IsEvaluating) {
2574  // FIXME: Produce a diagnostic for self-initialization.
2575  return nullptr;
2576  }
2577 
2578  Eval->IsEvaluating = true;
2579 
2580  ASTContext &Ctx = getASTContext();
2581  bool Result = Init->EvaluateAsInitializer(Eval->Evaluated, Ctx, this, Notes,
2582  IsConstantInitialization);
2583 
2584  // In C++, or in C23 if we're initialising a 'constexpr' variable, this isn't
2585  // a constant initializer if we produced notes. In that case, we can't keep
2586  // the result, because it may only be correct under the assumption that the
2587  // initializer is a constant context.
2588  if (IsConstantInitialization &&
2589  (Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ||
2590  (isConstexpr() && Ctx.getLangOpts().C23)) &&
2591  !Notes.empty())
2592  Result = false;
2593 
2594  // Ensure the computed APValue is cleaned up later if evaluation succeeded,
2595  // or that it's empty (so that there's nothing to clean up) if evaluation
2596  // failed.
2597  if (!Result)
2598  Eval->Evaluated = APValue();
2599  else if (Eval->Evaluated.needsCleanup())
2600  Ctx.addDestruction(&Eval->Evaluated);
2601 
2602  Eval->IsEvaluating = false;
2603  Eval->WasEvaluated = true;
2604 
2605  return Result ? &Eval->Evaluated : nullptr;
2606 }
2607 
2608 APValue *VarDecl::getEvaluatedValue() const {
2609  if (EvaluatedStmt *Eval = getEvaluatedStmt())
2610  if (Eval->WasEvaluated)
2611  return &Eval->Evaluated;
2612 
2613  return nullptr;
2614 }
2615 
2616 bool VarDecl::hasICEInitializer(const ASTContext &Context) const {
2617  const Expr *Init = getInit();
2618  assert(Init && "no initializer");
2619 
2620  EvaluatedStmt *Eval = ensureEvaluatedStmt();
2621  if (!Eval->CheckedForICEInit) {
2622  Eval->CheckedForICEInit = true;
2623  Eval->HasICEInit = Init->isIntegerConstantExpr(Context);
2624  }
2625  return Eval->HasICEInit;
2626 }
2627 
2628 bool VarDecl::hasConstantInitialization() const {
2629  // In C, all globals (and only globals) have constant initialization.
2630  if (hasGlobalStorage() && !getASTContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
2631  return true;
2632 
2633  // In C++, it depends on whether the evaluation at the point of definition
2634  // was evaluatable as a constant initializer.
2635  if (EvaluatedStmt *Eval = getEvaluatedStmt())
2636  return Eval->HasConstantInitialization;
2637 
2638  return false;
2639 }
2640 
2641 bool VarDecl::checkForConstantInitialization(
2642  SmallVectorImpl<PartialDiagnosticAt> &Notes) const {
2643  EvaluatedStmt *Eval = ensureEvaluatedStmt();
2644  // If we ask for the value before we know whether we have a constant
2645  // initializer, we can compute the wrong value (for example, due to
2646  // std::is_constant_evaluated()).
2647  assert(!Eval->WasEvaluated &&
2648  "already evaluated var value before checking for constant init");
2649  assert((getASTContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ||
2650  getASTContext().getLangOpts().C23) &&
2651  "only meaningful in C++/C23");
2652 
2653  assert(!getInit()->isValueDependent());
2654 
2655  // Evaluate the initializer to check whether it's a constant expression.
2656  Eval->HasConstantInitialization =
2657  evaluateValueImpl(Notes, true) && Notes.empty();
2658 
2659  // If evaluation as a constant initializer failed, allow re-evaluation as a
2660  // non-constant initializer if we later find we want the value.
2661  if (!Eval->HasConstantInitialization)
2662  Eval->WasEvaluated = false;
2663 
2664  return Eval->HasConstantInitialization;
2665 }
2666 
2667 bool VarDecl::isParameterPack() const {
2668  return isa<PackExpansionType>(getType());
2669 }

2671 template<typename DeclT>
2672 static DeclT *getDefinitionOrSelf(DeclT *D) {
2673  assert(D);
2674  if (auto *Def = D->getDefinition())
2675  return Def;
2676  return D;
2677 }

2687 bool VarDecl::hasDependentAlignment() const {
2688  QualType T = getType();
2689  return T->isDependentType() || T->isUndeducedType() ||
2690  llvm::any_of(specific_attrs<AlignedAttr>(), [](const AlignedAttr *AA) {
2691  return AA->isAlignmentDependent();
2692  });

2694 
2695 VarDecl *VarDecl::getTemplateInstantiationPattern() const {
2696  const VarDecl *VD = this;
2697 
2698  // If this is an instantiated member, walk back to the template from which
2699  // it was instantiated.
2700  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo = VD->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
2701  if (isTemplateInstantiation(MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind())) {
2702  VD = VD->getInstantiatedFromStaticDataMember();
2703  while (auto *NewVD = VD->getInstantiatedFromStaticDataMember())
2704  VD = NewVD;
2705  }
2706  }
2707 
2708  // If it's an instantiated variable template specialization, find the
2709  // template or partial specialization from which it was instantiated.
2710  if (auto *VDTemplSpec = dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(VD)) {
2711  if (isTemplateInstantiation(VDTemplSpec->getTemplateSpecializationKind())) {
2712  auto From = VDTemplSpec->getInstantiatedFrom();
2713  if (auto *VTD = From.dyn_cast<VarTemplateDecl *>()) {
2714  while (!VTD->isMemberSpecialization()) {
2715  auto *NewVTD = VTD->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate();
2716  if (!NewVTD)
2717  break;
2718  VTD = NewVTD;
2719  }
2720  return getDefinitionOrSelf(VTD->getTemplatedDecl());
2721  }
2722  if (auto *VTPSD =
2723  From.dyn_cast<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *>()) {
2724  while (!VTPSD->isMemberSpecialization()) {
2725  auto *NewVTPSD = VTPSD->getInstantiatedFromMember();
2726  if (!NewVTPSD)
2727  break;
2728  VTPSD = NewVTPSD;
2729  }
2730  return getDefinitionOrSelf<VarDecl>(VTPSD);
2731  }
2732  }
2733  }
2734 
2735  // If this is the pattern of a variable template, find where it was
2736  // instantiated from. FIXME: Is this necessary?
2737  if (VarTemplateDecl *VarTemplate = VD->getDescribedVarTemplate()) {
2738  while (!VarTemplate->isMemberSpecialization()) {
2739  auto *NewVT = VarTemplate->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate();
2740  if (!NewVT)
2741  break;
2742  VarTemplate = NewVT;
2743  }
2744 
2745  return getDefinitionOrSelf(VarTemplate->getTemplatedDecl());
2746  }
2747 
2748  if (VD == this)
2749  return nullptr;
2750  return getDefinitionOrSelf(const_cast<VarDecl*>(VD));
2751 }
2752 
2753 VarDecl *VarDecl::getInstantiatedFromStaticDataMember() const {
2754  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSI = getMemberSpecializationInfo())
2755  return cast<VarDecl>(MSI->getInstantiatedFrom());
2756 
2757  return nullptr;
2758 }
2759 
2760 TemplateSpecializationKind VarDecl::getTemplateSpecializationKind() const {
2761  if (const auto *Spec = dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(this))
2762  return Spec->getSpecializationKind();
2763 
2764  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSI = getMemberSpecializationInfo())
2765  return MSI->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
2766 
2767  return TSK_Undeclared;
2768 }
2769

2771 VarDecl::getTemplateSpecializationKindForInstantiation() const {
2772  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSI = getMemberSpecializationInfo())
2773  return MSI->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
2774 
2775  if (const auto *Spec = dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(this))
2776  return Spec->getSpecializationKind();
2777 
2778  return TSK_Undeclared;
2779 }

2800 bool VarDecl::isKnownToBeDefined() const {
2801  const auto &LangOpts = getASTContext().getLangOpts();
2802  // In CUDA mode without relocatable device code, variables of form 'extern
2803  // __shared__ Foo foo[]' are pointers to the base of the GPU core's shared
2804  // memory pool. These are never undefined variables, even if they appear
2805  // inside of an anon namespace or static function.
2806  //
2807  // With CUDA relocatable device code enabled, these variables don't get
2808  // special handling; they're treated like regular extern variables.
2809  if (LangOpts.CUDA && !LangOpts.GPURelocatableDeviceCode &&
2810  hasExternalStorage() && hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>() &&
2811  isa<IncompleteArrayType>(getType()))
2812  return true;
2813 
2814  return hasDefinition();
2815 }

2817 bool VarDecl::isNoDestroy(const ASTContext &Ctx) const {
2818  return hasGlobalStorage() && (hasAttr<NoDestroyAttr>() ||
2819  (!Ctx.getLangOpts().RegisterStaticDestructors &&
2820  !hasAttr<AlwaysDestroyAttr>()));
2821 }
2822 
2823 QualType::DestructionKind
2824 VarDecl::needsDestruction(const ASTContext &Ctx) const {
2825  if (EvaluatedStmt *Eval = getEvaluatedStmt())
2826  if (Eval->HasConstantDestruction)
2827  return QualType::DK_none;
2828 
2829  if (isNoDestroy(Ctx))
2830  return QualType::DK_none;
2831 
2832  return getType().isDestructedType();
2833 }
2834 
2835 bool VarDecl::hasFlexibleArrayInit(const ASTContext &Ctx) const {
2836  assert(hasInit() && "Expect initializer to check for flexible array init");
2837  auto *Ty = getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
2838  if (!Ty || !Ty->getDecl()->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
2839  return false;
2840  auto *List = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(getInit()->IgnoreParens());
2841  if (!List)
2842  return false;
2843  const Expr *FlexibleInit = List->getInit(List->getNumInits() - 1);
2844  auto InitTy = Ctx.getAsConstantArrayType(FlexibleInit->getType());
2845  if (!InitTy)
2846  return false;
2847  return !InitTy->isZeroSize();
2848 }
2849 
2850 CharUnits VarDecl::getFlexibleArrayInitChars(const ASTContext &Ctx) const {
2851  assert(hasInit() && "Expect initializer to check for flexible array init");
2852  auto *Ty = getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
2853  if (!Ty || !Ty->getDecl()->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
2854  return CharUnits::Zero();
2855  auto *List = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(getInit()->IgnoreParens());
2856  if (!List || List->getNumInits() == 0)
2857  return CharUnits::Zero();
2858  const Expr *FlexibleInit = List->getInit(List->getNumInits() - 1);
2859  auto InitTy = Ctx.getAsConstantArrayType(FlexibleInit->getType());
2860  if (!InitTy)
2861  return CharUnits::Zero();
2862  CharUnits FlexibleArraySize = Ctx.getTypeSizeInChars(InitTy);
2863  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(Ty->getDecl());
2864  CharUnits FlexibleArrayOffset =
2865  Ctx.toCharUnitsFromBits(RL.getFieldOffset(RL.getFieldCount() - 1));
2866  if (FlexibleArrayOffset + FlexibleArraySize < RL.getSize())
2867  return CharUnits::Zero();
2868  return FlexibleArrayOffset + FlexibleArraySize - RL.getSize();
2869 }

2875  return getASTContext().getTemplateOrSpecializationInfo(this)
2876  .dyn_cast<MemberSpecializationInfo *>();
2877  return nullptr;
2878 }

2880 void VarDecl::setTemplateSpecializationKind(TemplateSpecializationKind TSK,
2881  SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation) {
2882  assert((isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(this) ||
2883  getMemberSpecializationInfo()) &&
2884  "not a variable or static data member template specialization");
2885 
2886  if (VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *Spec =
2887  dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(this)) {
2888  Spec->setSpecializationKind(TSK);
2889  if (TSK != TSK_ExplicitSpecialization &&
2890  PointOfInstantiation.isValid() &&
2891  Spec->getPointOfInstantiation().isInvalid()) {
2892  Spec->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
2893  if (ASTMutationListener *L = getASTContext().getASTMutationListener())
2894  L->InstantiationRequested(this);
2895  }
2896  } else if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSI = getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
2897  MSI->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK);
2898  if (TSK != TSK_ExplicitSpecialization && PointOfInstantiation.isValid() &&
2899  MSI->getPointOfInstantiation().isInvalid()) {
2900  MSI->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
2901  if (ASTMutationListener *L = getASTContext().getASTMutationListener())
2902  L->InstantiationRequested(this);
2903  }
2904  }
2905 }

2942 SourceRange ParmVarDecl::getSourceRange() const {
2943  if (!hasInheritedDefaultArg()) {
2944  SourceRange ArgRange = getDefaultArgRange();
2945  if (ArgRange.isValid())
2946  return SourceRange(getOuterLocStart(), ArgRange.getEnd());
2947  }
2948

2950  // declaration name, but this is not the case with parameters in ObjC methods.
2951  if (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(getDeclContext()))
2952  return SourceRange(DeclaratorDecl::getBeginLoc(), getLocation());
2953

2957 bool ParmVarDecl::isDestroyedInCallee() const {
2958  // ns_consumed only affects code generation in ARC

2960  return getASTContext().getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount;
2961 
2962  // FIXME: isParamDestroyedInCallee() should probably imply
2963  // isDestructedType()
2964  const auto *RT = getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
2965  if (RT && RT->getDecl()->isParamDestroyedInCallee() &&
2966  getType().isDestructedType())

2968 
2969  return false;

2972 Expr *ParmVarDecl::getDefaultArg() {

2975  "Default argument is not yet instantiated!");

2989 SourceRange ParmVarDecl::getDefaultArgRange() const {
2990  switch (ParmVarDeclBits.DefaultArgKind) {
2991  case DAK_None:
2992  case DAK_Unparsed:
2993  // Nothing we can do here.
2994  return SourceRange();
2995 
2996  case DAK_Uninstantiated:
2997  return getUninstantiatedDefaultArg()->getSourceRange();
2998 
2999  case DAK_Normal:
3000  if (const Expr *E = getInit())
3001  return E->getSourceRange();
3002 
3003  // Missing an actual expression, may be invalid.
3004  return SourceRange();
3005  }
3006  llvm_unreachable("Invalid default argument kind.");
3007 }

3011  Init = arg;
3012 }

3016  "Wrong kind of initialization expression!");

3018 }

3079  FunctionDeclBits.HasODRHash = false;

3081  if (TrailingRequiresClause)
3082  setTrailingRequiresClause(TrailingRequiresClause);
3083 }

3099 FunctionDecl::DefaultedOrDeletedFunctionInfo *
3100 FunctionDecl::DefaultedOrDeletedFunctionInfo::Create(
3101  ASTContext &Context, ArrayRef<DeclAccessPair> Lookups,
3102  StringLiteral *DeletedMessage) {
3103  static constexpr size_t Alignment =
3104  std::max({alignof(DefaultedOrDeletedFunctionInfo),
3105  alignof(DeclAccessPair), alignof(StringLiteral *)});
3106  size_t Size = totalSizeToAlloc<DeclAccessPair, StringLiteral *>(
3107  Lookups.size(), DeletedMessage != nullptr);
3108 
3109  DefaultedOrDeletedFunctionInfo *Info =
3110  new (Context.Allocate(Size, Alignment)) DefaultedOrDeletedFunctionInfo;
3111  Info->NumLookups = Lookups.size();
3112  Info->HasDeletedMessage = DeletedMessage != nullptr;
3113 
3114  std::uninitialized_copy(Lookups.begin(), Lookups.end(),
3115  Info->getTrailingObjects<DeclAccessPair>());
3116  if (DeletedMessage)
3117  *Info->getTrailingObjects<StringLiteral *>() = DeletedMessage;
3118  return Info;
3119 }

3124  assert(!Body && "can't replace function body with defaulted function info");

3127  DefaultedOrDeletedInfo = Info;

3143 void FunctionDecl::DefaultedOrDeletedFunctionInfo::setDeletedMessage(

3145  // We should never get here with the DefaultedOrDeletedInfo populated, but
3146  // no space allocated for the deleted message, since that would require
3147  // recreating this, but setDefaultedOrDeletedInfo() disallows overwriting
3148  // an already existing DefaultedOrDeletedFunctionInfo.
3149  assert(HasDeletedMessage &&

3184 bool FunctionDecl::isThisDeclarationInstantiatedFromAFriendDefinition() const {
3185  if (!getFriendObjectKind())
3186  return false;
3187 
3188  // Check for a friend function instantiated from a friend function
3189  // definition in a templated class.
3190  if (const FunctionDecl *InstantiatedFrom =
3191  getInstantiatedFromMemberFunction())
3192  return InstantiatedFrom->getFriendObjectKind() &&
3193  InstantiatedFrom->isThisDeclarationADefinition();
3194 
3195  // Check for a friend function template instantiated from a friend
3196  // function template definition in a templated class.
3197  if (const FunctionTemplateDecl *Template = getDescribedFunctionTemplate()) {
3198  if (const FunctionTemplateDecl *InstantiatedFrom =
3199  Template->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate())
3200  return InstantiatedFrom->getFriendObjectKind() &&
3201  InstantiatedFrom->isThisDeclarationADefinition();
3202  }
3203 
3204  return false;
3205 }

3207 bool FunctionDecl::isDefined(const FunctionDecl *&Definition,
3208  bool CheckForPendingFriendDefinition) const {
3209  for (const FunctionDecl *FD : redecls()) {
3210  if (FD->isThisDeclarationADefinition()) {
3211  Definition = FD;
3212  return true;
3213  }
3214 
3215  // If this is a friend function defined in a class template, it does not
3216  // have a body until it is used, nevertheless it is a definition, see
3217  // [temp.inst]p2:
3218  //
3219  // ... for the purpose of determining whether an instantiated redeclaration
3220  // is valid according to [basic.def.odr] and [class.mem], a declaration that
3221  // corresponds to a definition in the template is considered to be a
3222  // definition.
3223  //
3224  // The following code must produce redefinition error:
3225  //
3226  // template<typename T> struct C20 { friend void func_20() {} };
3227  // C20<int> c20i;
3228  // void func_20() {}
3229  //
3230  if (CheckForPendingFriendDefinition &&
3231  FD->isThisDeclarationInstantiatedFromAFriendDefinition()) {
3232  Definition = FD;
3233  return true;
3234  }
3235  }
3236 
3237  return false;
3238 }

3245  "definition should not have a body");

3247  return Definition->Body.get(getASTContext().getExternalSource());
3248 
3249  return nullptr;

3272 bool FunctionDecl::isImmediateEscalating() const {
3273  // C++23 [expr.const]/p17
3274  // An immediate-escalating function is
3275  // - the call operator of a lambda that is not declared with the consteval
3276  // specifier,
3277  if (isLambdaCallOperator(this) && !isConsteval())
3278  return true;
3279  // - a defaulted special member function that is not declared with the
3280  // consteval specifier,
3281  if (isDefaulted() && !isConsteval())
3282  return true;
3283  // - a function that results from the instantiation of a templated entity
3284  // defined with the constexpr specifier.
3285  TemplatedKind TK = getTemplatedKind();
3286  if (TK != TK_NonTemplate && TK != TK_DependentNonTemplate &&
3287  isConstexprSpecified())
3288  return true;
3289  return false;
3290 }
3291 
3292 bool FunctionDecl::isImmediateFunction() const {
3293  // C++23 [expr.const]/p18
3294  // An immediate function is a function or constructor that is
3295  // - declared with the consteval specifier
3296  if (isConsteval())
3297  return true;
3298  // - an immediate-escalating function F whose function body contains an
3299  // immediate-escalating expression
3300  if (isImmediateEscalating() && BodyContainsImmediateEscalatingExpressions())
3301  return true;
3302 
3303  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(this);
3304  MD && MD->isLambdaStaticInvoker())
3305  return MD->getParent()->getLambdaCallOperator()->isImmediateFunction();
3306 
3307  return false;
3308 }

3318 bool FunctionDecl::isMSVCRTEntryPoint() const {
3319  const TranslationUnitDecl *TUnit =
3320  dyn_cast<TranslationUnitDecl>(getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext());
3321  if (!TUnit)
3322  return false;
3323 
3324  // Even though we aren't really targeting MSVCRT if we are freestanding,
3325  // semantic analysis for these functions remains the same.
3326 
3327  // MSVCRT entry points only exist on MSVCRT targets.
3328  if (!TUnit->getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSMSVCRT())
3329  return false;
3330 
3331  // Nameless functions like constructors cannot be entry points.
3332  if (!getIdentifier())
3333  return false;
3334 
3335  return llvm::StringSwitch<bool>(getName())
3336  .Cases("main", // an ANSI console app
3337  "wmain", // a Unicode console App
3338  "WinMain", // an ANSI GUI app
3339  "wWinMain", // a Unicode GUI app
3340  "DllMain", // a DLL
3341  true)
3342  .Default(false);
3343 }

3345 bool FunctionDecl::isReservedGlobalPlacementOperator() const {
3346  if (getDeclName().getNameKind() != DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName)
3347  return false;
3348  if (getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_New &&
3349  getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_Delete &&
3350  getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_Array_New &&
3351  getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_Array_Delete)
3352  return false;
3353 
3354  if (!getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()->isTranslationUnit())
3355  return false;
3356 
3357  const auto *proto = getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
3358  if (proto->getNumParams() != 2 || proto->isVariadic())
3359  return false;
3360 
3361  const ASTContext &Context =
3362  cast<TranslationUnitDecl>(getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext())
3363  ->getASTContext();
3364 
3365  // The result type and first argument type are constant across all
3366  // these operators. The second argument must be exactly void*.
3367  return (proto->getParamType(1).getCanonicalType() == Context.VoidPtrTy);
3368 }
3369 
3370 bool FunctionDecl::isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction(
3371  std::optional<unsigned> *AlignmentParam, bool *IsNothrow) const {
3372  if (getDeclName().getNameKind() != DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName)
3373  return false;
3374  if (getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_New &&
3375  getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_Delete &&
3376  getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_Array_New &&
3377  getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_Array_Delete)
3378  return false;
3379 
3380  if (isa<CXXRecordDecl>(getDeclContext()))
3381  return false;
3382 
3383  // This can only fail for an invalid 'operator new' declaration.
3384  if (!getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()->isTranslationUnit())
3385  return false;
3386 
3387  const auto *FPT = getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
3388  if (FPT->getNumParams() == 0 || FPT->getNumParams() > 4 || FPT->isVariadic())
3389  return false;
3390 
3391  // If this is a single-parameter function, it must be a replaceable global
3392  // allocation or deallocation function.
3393  if (FPT->getNumParams() == 1)
3394  return true;
3395 
3396  unsigned Params = 1;
3397  QualType Ty = FPT->getParamType(Params);
3398  const ASTContext &Ctx = getASTContext();
3399 
3400  auto Consume = [&] {
3401  ++Params;
3402  Ty = Params < FPT->getNumParams() ? FPT->getParamType(Params) : QualType();
3403  };
3404 
3405  // In C++14, the next parameter can be a 'std::size_t' for sized delete.
3406  bool IsSizedDelete = false;
3407  if (Ctx.getLangOpts().SizedDeallocation &&
3408  (getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() == OO_Delete ||
3409  getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() == OO_Array_Delete) &&
3410  Ctx.hasSameType(Ty, Ctx.getSizeType())) {
3411  IsSizedDelete = true;
3412  Consume();
3413  }
3414 
3415  // In C++17, the next parameter can be a 'std::align_val_t' for aligned
3416  // new/delete.
3417  if (Ctx.getLangOpts().AlignedAllocation && !Ty.isNull() && Ty->isAlignValT()) {
3418  Consume();
3419  if (AlignmentParam)
3420  *AlignmentParam = Params;
3421  }
3422 
3423  // If this is not a sized delete, the next parameter can be a
3424  // 'const std::nothrow_t&'.
3425  if (!IsSizedDelete && !Ty.isNull() && Ty->isReferenceType()) {
3426  Ty = Ty->getPointeeType();
3427  if (Ty.getCVRQualifiers() != Qualifiers::Const)
3428  return false;
3429  if (Ty->isNothrowT()) {
3430  if (IsNothrow)
3431  *IsNothrow = true;
3432  Consume();
3433  }
3434  }
3435 
3436  // Finally, recognize the not yet standard versions of new that take a
3437  // hot/cold allocation hint (__hot_cold_t). These are currently supported by
3438  // tcmalloc (see
3439  // https://github.com/google/tcmalloc/blob/220043886d4e2efff7a5702d5172cb8065253664/tcmalloc/malloc_extension.h#L53).
3440  if (!IsSizedDelete && !Ty.isNull() && Ty->isEnumeralType()) {
3441  QualType T = Ty;
3442  while (const auto *TD = T->getAs<TypedefType>())
3443  T = TD->getDecl()->getUnderlyingType();
3444  const IdentifierInfo *II =
3445  T->castAs<EnumType>()->getDecl()->getIdentifier();
3446  if (II && II->isStr("__hot_cold_t"))
3447  Consume();
3448  }
3449 
3450  return Params == FPT->getNumParams();
3451 }
3452 
3453 bool FunctionDecl::isInlineBuiltinDeclaration() const {
3454  if (!getBuiltinID())
3455  return false;
3456 
3457  const FunctionDecl *Definition;
3458  if (!hasBody(Definition))
3459  return false;
3460 
3461  if (!Definition->isInlineSpecified() ||
3462  !Definition->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>())
3463  return false;
3464 
3465  ASTContext &Context = getASTContext();
3466  switch (Context.GetGVALinkageForFunction(Definition)) {
3467  case GVA_Internal:
3468  case GVA_DiscardableODR:
3469  case GVA_StrongODR:
3470  return false;
3471  case GVA_AvailableExternally:
3472  case GVA_StrongExternal:
3473  return true;
3474  }
3475  llvm_unreachable("Unknown GVALinkage");
3476 }

3478 bool FunctionDecl::isDestroyingOperatorDelete() const {
3479  // C++ P0722:
3480  // Within a class C, a single object deallocation function with signature
3481  // (T, std::destroying_delete_t, <more params>)
3482  // is a destroying operator delete.
3483  if (!isa<CXXMethodDecl>(this) || getOverloadedOperator() != OO_Delete ||
3484  getNumParams() < 2)
3485  return false;
3486 
3487  auto *RD = getParamDecl(1)->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3488  return RD && RD->isInStdNamespace() && RD->getIdentifier() &&
3489  RD->getIdentifier()->isStr("destroying_delete_t");
3490 }

3540 bool FunctionDecl::isMemberLikeConstrainedFriend() const {
3541  // C++20 [temp.friend]p9:
3542  // A non-template friend declaration with a requires-clause [or]
3543  // a friend function template with a constraint that depends on a template
3544  // parameter from an enclosing template [...] does not declare the same
3545  // function or function template as a declaration in any other scope.
3546 
3547  // If this isn't a friend then it's not a member-like constrained friend.
3548  if (!getFriendObjectKind()) {
3549  return false;
3550  }
3551 
3552  if (!getDescribedFunctionTemplate()) {
3553  // If these friends don't have constraints, they aren't constrained, and
3554  // thus don't fall under temp.friend p9. Else the simple presence of a
3555  // constraint makes them unique.
3556  return getTrailingRequiresClause();
3557  }
3558 
3559  return FriendConstraintRefersToEnclosingTemplate();
3560 }

3621 FunctionDecl *FunctionDecl::getCanonicalDecl() { return getFirstDecl(); }

3623 /// Returns a value indicating whether this function corresponds to a builtin
3624 /// function.
3625 ///
3626 /// The function corresponds to a built-in function if it is declared at
3627 /// translation scope or within an extern "C" block and its name matches with
3628 /// the name of a builtin. The returned value will be 0 for functions that do
3629 /// not correspond to a builtin, a value of type \c Builtin::ID if in the
3630 /// target-independent range \c [1,Builtin::First), or a target-specific builtin
3631 /// value.
3632 ///
3633 /// \param ConsiderWrapperFunctions If true, we should consider wrapper
3634 /// functions as their wrapped builtins. This shouldn't be done in general, but
3635 /// it's useful in Sema to diagnose calls to wrappers based on their semantics.
3636 unsigned FunctionDecl::getBuiltinID(bool ConsiderWrapperFunctions) const {
3637  unsigned BuiltinID = 0;
3638 
3639  if (const auto *ABAA = getAttr<ArmBuiltinAliasAttr>()) {
3640  BuiltinID = ABAA->getBuiltinName()->getBuiltinID();
3641  } else if (const auto *BAA = getAttr<BuiltinAliasAttr>()) {
3642  BuiltinID = BAA->getBuiltinName()->getBuiltinID();
3643  } else if (const auto *A = getAttr<BuiltinAttr>()) {
3644  BuiltinID = A->getID();
3645  }
3646 
3647  if (!BuiltinID)
3648  return 0;
3649 
3650  // If the function is marked "overloadable", it has a different mangled name
3651  // and is not the C library function.
3652  if (!ConsiderWrapperFunctions && hasAttr<OverloadableAttr>() &&
3653  (!hasAttr<ArmBuiltinAliasAttr>() && !hasAttr<BuiltinAliasAttr>()))
3654  return 0;
3655 
3656  const ASTContext &Context = getASTContext();
3657  if (!Context.BuiltinInfo.isPredefinedLibFunction(BuiltinID))
3658  return BuiltinID;
3659 
3660  // This function has the name of a known C library
3661  // function. Determine whether it actually refers to the C library
3662  // function or whether it just has the same name.
3663 
3664  // If this is a static function, it's not a builtin.
3665  if (!ConsiderWrapperFunctions && getStorageClass() == SC_Static)
3666  return 0;
3667 
3668  // OpenCL v1.2 s6.9.f - The library functions defined in
3669  // the C99 standard headers are not available.
3670  if (Context.getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
3671  Context.BuiltinInfo.isPredefinedLibFunction(BuiltinID))
3672  return 0;
3673 
3674  // CUDA does not have device-side standard library. printf and malloc are the
3675  // only special cases that are supported by device-side runtime.
3676  if (Context.getLangOpts().CUDA && hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() &&
3677  !hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>() &&
3678  !(BuiltinID == Builtin::BIprintf || BuiltinID == Builtin::BImalloc))
3679  return 0;
3680 
3681  // As AMDGCN implementation of OpenMP does not have a device-side standard
3682  // library, none of the predefined library functions except printf and malloc
3683  // should be treated as a builtin i.e. 0 should be returned for them.
3684  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isAMDGCN() &&
3685  Context.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice &&
3686  Context.BuiltinInfo.isPredefinedLibFunction(BuiltinID) &&
3687  !(BuiltinID == Builtin::BIprintf || BuiltinID == Builtin::BImalloc))
3688  return 0;
3689 
3690  return BuiltinID;
3691 }
3692 
3693 /// getNumParams - Return the number of parameters this function must have
3694 /// based on its FunctionType. This is the length of the ParamInfo array
3695 /// after it has been created.
3696 unsigned FunctionDecl::getNumParams() const {
3697  const auto *FPT = getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
3698  return FPT ? FPT->getNumParams() : 0;
3699 }
3700 
3701 void FunctionDecl::setParams(ASTContext &C,
3702  ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> NewParamInfo) {
3703  assert(!ParamInfo && "Already has param info!");
3704  assert(NewParamInfo.size() == getNumParams() && "Parameter count mismatch!");
3705 
3706  // Zero params -> null pointer.
3707  if (!NewParamInfo.empty()) {
3708  ParamInfo = new (C) ParmVarDecl*[NewParamInfo.size()];
3709  std::copy(NewParamInfo.begin(), NewParamInfo.end(), ParamInfo);
3710  }
3711 }

3713 /// getMinRequiredArguments - Returns the minimum number of arguments
3714 /// needed to call this function. This may be fewer than the number of
3715 /// function parameters, if some of the parameters have default
3716 /// arguments (in C++) or are parameter packs (C++11).
3717 unsigned FunctionDecl::getMinRequiredArguments() const {
3718  if (!getASTContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
3719  return getNumParams();
3720 
3721  // Note that it is possible for a parameter with no default argument to
3722  // follow a parameter with a default argument.
3723  unsigned NumRequiredArgs = 0;
3724  unsigned MinParamsSoFar = 0;
3725  for (auto *Param : parameters()) {
3726  if (!Param->isParameterPack()) {
3727  ++MinParamsSoFar;
3728  if (!Param->hasDefaultArg())
3729  NumRequiredArgs = MinParamsSoFar;
3730  }
3731  }
3732  return NumRequiredArgs;
3733 }
3734 
3735 bool FunctionDecl::hasCXXExplicitFunctionObjectParameter() const {
3736  return getNumParams() != 0 && getParamDecl(0)->isExplicitObjectParameter();
3737 }
3738 
3739 unsigned FunctionDecl::getNumNonObjectParams() const {
3740  return getNumParams() -
3741  static_cast<unsigned>(hasCXXExplicitFunctionObjectParameter());
3742 }
3743 
3744 unsigned FunctionDecl::getMinRequiredExplicitArguments() const {
3745  return getMinRequiredArguments() -
3746  static_cast<unsigned>(hasCXXExplicitFunctionObjectParameter());
3747 }

3749 bool FunctionDecl::hasOneParamOrDefaultArgs() const {
3750  return getNumParams() == 1 ||
3751  (getNumParams() > 1 &&
3752  llvm::all_of(llvm::drop_begin(parameters()),
3753  [](ParmVarDecl *P) { return P->hasDefaultArg(); }));
3754 }

3756 /// The combination of the extern and inline keywords under MSVC forces
3757 /// the function to be required.
3758 ///
3759 /// Note: This function assumes that we will only get called when isInlined()
3760 /// would return true for this FunctionDecl.
3761 bool FunctionDecl::isMSExternInline() const {
3762  assert(isInlined() && "expected to get called on an inlined function!");
3763 
3764  const ASTContext &Context = getASTContext();
3765  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
3766  !hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
3767  return false;
3768 
3769  for (const FunctionDecl *FD = getMostRecentDecl(); FD;
3770  FD = FD->getPreviousDecl())
3771  if (!FD->isImplicit() && FD->getStorageClass() == SC_Extern)
3772  return true;
3773 
3774  return false;
3775 }
3776 
3777 static bool redeclForcesDefMSVC(const FunctionDecl *Redecl) {
3778  if (Redecl->getStorageClass() != SC_Extern)
3779  return false;
3780 
3781  for (const FunctionDecl *FD = Redecl->getPreviousDecl(); FD;
3782  FD = FD->getPreviousDecl())
3783  if (!FD->isImplicit() && FD->getStorageClass() == SC_Extern)
3784  return false;
3785 
3786  return true;
3787 }
3788 
3789 static bool RedeclForcesDefC99(const FunctionDecl *Redecl) {
3790  // Only consider file-scope declarations in this test.
3791  if (!Redecl->getLexicalDeclContext()->isTranslationUnit())
3792  return false;
3793 
3794  // Only consider explicit declarations; the presence of a builtin for a
3795  // libcall shouldn't affect whether a definition is externally visible.
3796  if (Redecl->isImplicit())
3797  return false;
3798 
3799  if (!Redecl->isInlineSpecified() || Redecl->getStorageClass() == SC_Extern)
3800  return true; // Not an inline definition
3801 
3802  return false;
3803 }
3804 
3805 /// For a function declaration in C or C++, determine whether this
3806 /// declaration causes the definition to be externally visible.
3807 ///
3808 /// For instance, this determines if adding the current declaration to the set
3809 /// of redeclarations of the given functions causes
3810 /// isInlineDefinitionExternallyVisible to change from false to true.
3811 bool FunctionDecl::doesDeclarationForceExternallyVisibleDefinition() const {
3812  assert(!doesThisDeclarationHaveABody() &&
3813  "Must have a declaration without a body.");
3814 
3815  const ASTContext &Context = getASTContext();
3816 
3817  if (Context.getLangOpts().MSVCCompat) {
3818  const FunctionDecl *Definition;
3819  if (hasBody(Definition) && Definition->isInlined() &&
3820  redeclForcesDefMSVC(this))
3821  return true;
3822  }
3823 
3824  if (Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
3825  return false;
3826 
3827  if (Context.getLangOpts().GNUInline || hasAttr<GNUInlineAttr>()) {
3828  // With GNU inlining, a declaration with 'inline' but not 'extern', forces
3829  // an externally visible definition.
3830  //
3831  // FIXME: What happens if gnu_inline gets added on after the first
3832  // declaration?
3833  if (!isInlineSpecified() || getStorageClass() == SC_Extern)
3834  return false;
3835 
3836  const FunctionDecl *Prev = this;
3837  bool FoundBody = false;
3838  while ((Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl())) {
3839  FoundBody |= Prev->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody();
3840 
3841  if (Prev->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody()) {
3842  // If it's not the case that both 'inline' and 'extern' are
3843  // specified on the definition, then it is always externally visible.
3844  if (!Prev->isInlineSpecified() ||
3845  Prev->getStorageClass() != SC_Extern)
3846  return false;
3847  } else if (Prev->isInlineSpecified() &&
3848  Prev->getStorageClass() != SC_Extern) {
3849  return false;
3850  }
3851  }
3852  return FoundBody;
3853  }
3854 
3855  // C99 6.7.4p6:
3856  // [...] If all of the file scope declarations for a function in a
3857  // translation unit include the inline function specifier without extern,
3858  // then the definition in that translation unit is an inline definition.
3859  if (isInlineSpecified() && getStorageClass() != SC_Extern)
3860  return false;
3861  const FunctionDecl *Prev = this;
3862  bool FoundBody = false;
3863  while ((Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl())) {
3864  FoundBody |= Prev->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody();
3865  if (RedeclForcesDefC99(Prev))
3866  return false;
3867  }
3868  return FoundBody;
3869 }
3870 
3871 FunctionTypeLoc FunctionDecl::getFunctionTypeLoc() const {
3872  const TypeSourceInfo *TSI = getTypeSourceInfo();
3873  return TSI ? TSI->getTypeLoc().IgnoreParens().getAs<FunctionTypeLoc>()
3874  : FunctionTypeLoc();
3875 }
3876 
3877 SourceRange FunctionDecl::getReturnTypeSourceRange() const {
3878  FunctionTypeLoc FTL = getFunctionTypeLoc();
3879  if (!FTL)
3880  return SourceRange();
3881 
3882  // Skip self-referential return types.
3883  const SourceManager &SM = getASTContext().getSourceManager();
3884  SourceRange RTRange = FTL.getReturnLoc().getSourceRange();
3885  SourceLocation Boundary = getNameInfo().getBeginLoc();
3886  if (RTRange.isInvalid() || Boundary.isInvalid() ||
3887  !SM.isBeforeInTranslationUnit(RTRange.getEnd(), Boundary))
3888  return SourceRange();
3889 
3890  return RTRange;
3891 }
3892 
3893 SourceRange FunctionDecl::getParametersSourceRange() const {
3894  unsigned NP = getNumParams();
3895  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc = getEllipsisLoc();
3896 
3897  if (NP == 0 && EllipsisLoc.isInvalid())
3898  return SourceRange();
3899 
3900  SourceLocation Begin =
3901  NP > 0 ? ParamInfo[0]->getSourceRange().getBegin() : EllipsisLoc;
3902  SourceLocation End = EllipsisLoc.isValid()
3903  ? EllipsisLoc
3904  : ParamInfo[NP - 1]->getSourceRange().getEnd();
3905 
3906  return SourceRange(Begin, End);
3907 }

3909 SourceRange FunctionDecl::getExceptionSpecSourceRange() const {
3910  FunctionTypeLoc FTL = getFunctionTypeLoc();
3911  return FTL ? FTL.getExceptionSpecRange() : SourceRange();
3912 }
3913 
3914 /// For an inline function definition in C, or for a gnu_inline function
3915 /// in C++, determine whether the definition will be externally visible.
3916 ///
3917 /// Inline function definitions are always available for inlining optimizations.
3918 /// However, depending on the language dialect, declaration specifiers, and
3919 /// attributes, the definition of an inline function may or may not be
3920 /// "externally" visible to other translation units in the program.
3921 ///
3922 /// In C99, inline definitions are not externally visible by default. However,
3923 /// if even one of the global-scope declarations is marked "extern inline", the
3924 /// inline definition becomes externally visible (C99 6.7.4p6).
3925 ///
3926 /// In GNU89 mode, or if the gnu_inline attribute is attached to the function
3927 /// definition, we use the GNU semantics for inline, which are nearly the
3928 /// opposite of C99 semantics. In particular, "inline" by itself will create
3929 /// an externally visible symbol, but "extern inline" will not create an
3930 /// externally visible symbol.
3931 bool FunctionDecl::isInlineDefinitionExternallyVisible() const {
3932  assert((doesThisDeclarationHaveABody() || willHaveBody() ||
3933  hasAttr<AliasAttr>()) &&
3934  "Must be a function definition");
3935  assert(isInlined() && "Function must be inline");
3936  ASTContext &Context = getASTContext();
3937 
3938  if (Context.getLangOpts().GNUInline || hasAttr<GNUInlineAttr>()) {
3939  // Note: If you change the logic here, please change
3940  // doesDeclarationForceExternallyVisibleDefinition as well.
3941  //
3942  // If it's not the case that both 'inline' and 'extern' are
3943  // specified on the definition, then this inline definition is
3944  // externally visible.
3945  if (Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
3946  return false;
3947  if (!(isInlineSpecified() && getStorageClass() == SC_Extern))
3948  return true;
3949 
3950  // If any declaration is 'inline' but not 'extern', then this definition
3951  // is externally visible.
3952  for (auto *Redecl : redecls()) {
3953  if (Redecl->isInlineSpecified() &&
3954  Redecl->getStorageClass() != SC_Extern)
3955  return true;
3956  }
3957 
3958  return false;
3959  }
3960 
3961  // The rest of this function is C-only.
3962  assert(!Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
3963  "should not use C inline rules in C++");
3964 
3965  // C99 6.7.4p6:
3966  // [...] If all of the file scope declarations for a function in a
3967  // translation unit include the inline function specifier without extern,
3968  // then the definition in that translation unit is an inline definition.
3969  for (auto *Redecl : redecls()) {
3970  if (RedeclForcesDefC99(Redecl))
3971  return true;
3972  }
3973 
3974  // C99 6.7.4p6:
3975  // An inline definition does not provide an external definition for the
3976  // function, and does not forbid an external definition in another
3977  // translation unit.
3978  return false;
3979 }

3997 FunctionDecl::TemplatedKind FunctionDecl::getTemplatedKind() const {
3998  if (TemplateOrSpecialization.isNull())
3999  return TK_NonTemplate;
4000  if (const auto *ND = TemplateOrSpecialization.dyn_cast<NamedDecl *>()) {
4001  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(ND))
4002  return TK_DependentNonTemplate;
4003  assert(isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(ND) &&
4004  "No other valid types in NamedDecl");
4005  return TK_FunctionTemplate;
4006  }
4007  if (TemplateOrSpecialization.is<MemberSpecializationInfo *>())
4008  return TK_MemberSpecialization;
4009  if (TemplateOrSpecialization.is<FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *>())
4010  return TK_FunctionTemplateSpecialization;
4011  if (TemplateOrSpecialization.is
4012  <DependentFunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo*>())
4013  return TK_DependentFunctionTemplateSpecialization;
4014 
4015  llvm_unreachable("Did we miss a TemplateOrSpecialization type?");
4016 }

4075 bool FunctionDecl::isImplicitlyInstantiable() const {
4076  // If the function is invalid, it can't be implicitly instantiated.
4077  if (isInvalidDecl())
4078  return false;
4079 
4080  switch (getTemplateSpecializationKindForInstantiation()) {
4081  case TSK_Undeclared:
4082  case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
4083  case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
4084  return false;
4085 
4086  case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
4087  return true;
4088 
4089  case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
4090  // Handled below.
4091  break;
4092  }
4093 
4094  // Find the actual template from which we will instantiate.
4095  const FunctionDecl *PatternDecl = getTemplateInstantiationPattern();
4096  bool HasPattern = false;
4097  if (PatternDecl)
4098  HasPattern = PatternDecl->hasBody(PatternDecl);
4099 
4100  // C++0x [temp.explicit]p9:
4101  // Except for inline functions, other explicit instantiation declarations
4102  // have the effect of suppressing the implicit instantiation of the entity
4103  // to which they refer.
4104  if (!HasPattern || !PatternDecl)
4105  return true;
4106 
4107  return PatternDecl->isInlined();
4108 }
4109 
4110 bool FunctionDecl::isTemplateInstantiation() const {
4111  // FIXME: Remove this, it's not clear what it means. (Which template
4112  // specialization kind?)
4113  return clang::isTemplateInstantiation(getTemplateSpecializationKind());
4114 }
4115 
4116 FunctionDecl *
4117 FunctionDecl::getTemplateInstantiationPattern(bool ForDefinition) const {
4118  // If this is a generic lambda call operator specialization, its
4119  // instantiation pattern is always its primary template's pattern
4120  // even if its primary template was instantiated from another
4121  // member template (which happens with nested generic lambdas).
4122  // Since a lambda's call operator's body is transformed eagerly,
4123  // we don't have to go hunting for a prototype definition template
4124  // (i.e. instantiated-from-member-template) to use as an instantiation
4125  // pattern.
4126 
4127  if (isGenericLambdaCallOperatorSpecialization(
4128  dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(this))) {
4129  assert(getPrimaryTemplate() && "not a generic lambda call operator?");
4130  return getDefinitionOrSelf(getPrimaryTemplate()->getTemplatedDecl());
4131  }
4132 
4133  // Check for a declaration of this function that was instantiated from a
4134  // friend definition.
4135  const FunctionDecl *FD = nullptr;
4136  if (!isDefined(FD, /*CheckForPendingFriendDefinition=*/true))
4137  FD = this;
4138 
4139  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *Info = FD->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
4140  if (ForDefinition &&
4141  !clang::isTemplateInstantiation(Info->getTemplateSpecializationKind()))
4142  return nullptr;
4143  return getDefinitionOrSelf(cast<FunctionDecl>(Info->getInstantiatedFrom()));
4144  }
4145 
4146  if (ForDefinition &&
4147  !clang::isTemplateInstantiation(getTemplateSpecializationKind()))
4148  return nullptr;
4149 
4150  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *Primary = getPrimaryTemplate()) {
4151  // If we hit a point where the user provided a specialization of this
4152  // template, we're done looking.
4153  while (!ForDefinition || !Primary->isMemberSpecialization()) {
4154  auto *NewPrimary = Primary->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate();
4155  if (!NewPrimary)
4156  break;
4157  Primary = NewPrimary;
4158  }
4159 
4160  return getDefinitionOrSelf(Primary->getTemplatedDecl());
4161  }
4162 
4163  return nullptr;
4164 }
4165

4171  }
4172  return nullptr;
4173 }

4206 void
4207 FunctionDecl::setFunctionTemplateSpecialization(ASTContext &C,
4208  FunctionTemplateDecl *Template,
4209  const TemplateArgumentList *TemplateArgs,
4210  void *InsertPos,
4211  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK,
4212  const TemplateArgumentListInfo *TemplateArgsAsWritten,
4213  SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation) {

4215  TemplateOrSpecialization.is<MemberSpecializationInfo *>()) &&
4216  "Member function is already a specialization");

4218  "Must specify the type of function template specialization");
4219  assert((TemplateOrSpecialization.isNull() ||
4220  getFriendObjectKind() != FOK_None ||
4221  TSK == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization) &&
4222  "Member specialization must be an explicit specialization");
4223  FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *Info =
4224  FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo::Create(
4225  C, this, Template, TSK, TemplateArgs, TemplateArgsAsWritten,

4248 DependentFunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *
4249 DependentFunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo::Create(
4250  ASTContext &Context, const UnresolvedSetImpl &Candidates,
4251  const TemplateArgumentListInfo *TArgs) {
4252  const auto *TArgsWritten =
4253  TArgs ? ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo::Create(Context, *TArgs) : nullptr;

4258 
4259 DependentFunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo::
4260  DependentFunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo(
4261  const UnresolvedSetImpl &Candidates,
4262  const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *TemplateArgsWritten)
4263  : NumCandidates(Candidates.size()),
4264  TemplateArgumentsAsWritten(TemplateArgsWritten) {
4265  std::transform(Candidates.begin(), Candidates.end(),
4266  getTrailingObjects<FunctionTemplateDecl *>(),
4267  [](NamedDecl *ND) {
4268  return cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(ND->getUnderlyingDecl());
4269  });
4270 }

4272 TemplateSpecializationKind FunctionDecl::getTemplateSpecializationKind() const {
4273  // For a function template specialization, query the specialization
4274  // information object.
4275  if (FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *FTSInfo =
4276  TemplateOrSpecialization
4277  .dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *>())
4278  return FTSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
4279 
4280  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo =
4281  TemplateOrSpecialization.dyn_cast<MemberSpecializationInfo *>())
4282  return MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
4283 
4284  // A dependent function template specialization is an explicit specialization,
4285  // except when it's a friend declaration.
4286  if (TemplateOrSpecialization
4287  .is<DependentFunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *>() &&
4288  getFriendObjectKind() == FOK_None)
4289  return TSK_ExplicitSpecialization;
4290 
4291  return TSK_Undeclared;
4292 }
4293 
4294 TemplateSpecializationKind
4295 FunctionDecl::getTemplateSpecializationKindForInstantiation() const {
4296  // This is the same as getTemplateSpecializationKind(), except that for a
4297  // function that is both a function template specialization and a member
4298  // specialization, we prefer the member specialization information. Eg:
4299  //
4300  // template<typename T> struct A {
4301  // template<typename U> void f() {}
4302  // template<> void f<int>() {}
4303  // };
4304  //
4305  // Within the templated CXXRecordDecl, A<T>::f<int> is a dependent function
4306  // template specialization; both getTemplateSpecializationKind() and
4307  // getTemplateSpecializationKindForInstantiation() will return
4308  // TSK_ExplicitSpecialization.
4309  //
4310  // For A<int>::f<int>():
4311  // * getTemplateSpecializationKind() will return TSK_ExplicitSpecialization
4312  // * getTemplateSpecializationKindForInstantiation() will return
4313  // TSK_ImplicitInstantiation
4314  //
4315  // This reflects the facts that A<int>::f<int> is an explicit specialization
4316  // of A<int>::f, and that A<int>::f<int> should be implicitly instantiated
4317  // from A::f<int> if a definition is needed.
4318  if (FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *FTSInfo =
4319  TemplateOrSpecialization
4320  .dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *>()) {
4321  if (auto *MSInfo = FTSInfo->getMemberSpecializationInfo())
4322  return MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
4323  return FTSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
4324  }
4325 
4326  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo =
4327  TemplateOrSpecialization.dyn_cast<MemberSpecializationInfo *>())
4328  return MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
4329 
4330  if (TemplateOrSpecialization
4331  .is<DependentFunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *>() &&
4332  getFriendObjectKind() == FOK_None)
4333  return TSK_ExplicitSpecialization;
4334 
4335  return TSK_Undeclared;
4336 }
4337 
4338 void
4339 FunctionDecl::setTemplateSpecializationKind(TemplateSpecializationKind TSK,
4340  SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation) {
4341  if (FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *FTSInfo
4342  = TemplateOrSpecialization.dyn_cast<
4343  FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo*>()) {
4344  FTSInfo->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK);
4345  if (TSK != TSK_ExplicitSpecialization &&
4346  PointOfInstantiation.isValid() &&
4347  FTSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation().isInvalid()) {
4348  FTSInfo->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
4349  if (ASTMutationListener *L = getASTContext().getASTMutationListener())
4350  L->InstantiationRequested(this);
4351  }
4352  } else if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo
4353  = TemplateOrSpecialization.dyn_cast<MemberSpecializationInfo*>()) {
4354  MSInfo->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK);
4355  if (TSK != TSK_ExplicitSpecialization &&
4356  PointOfInstantiation.isValid() &&
4357  MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation().isInvalid()) {
4358  MSInfo->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
4359  if (ASTMutationListener *L = getASTContext().getASTMutationListener())
4360  L->InstantiationRequested(this);
4361  }
4362  } else
4363  llvm_unreachable("Function cannot have a template specialization kind");
4364 }
4365 
4366 SourceLocation FunctionDecl::getPointOfInstantiation() const {
4367  if (FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *FTSInfo
4368  = TemplateOrSpecialization.dyn_cast<
4369  FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo*>())
4370  return FTSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation();
4371  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo =
4372  TemplateOrSpecialization.dyn_cast<MemberSpecializationInfo *>())
4373  return MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation();
4374 
4375  return SourceLocation();
4376 }
4377 
4378 bool FunctionDecl::isOutOfLine() const {
4379  if (Decl::isOutOfLine())
4380  return true;
4381 
4382  // If this function was instantiated from a member function of a
4383  // class template, check whether that member function was defined out-of-line.
4384  if (FunctionDecl *FD = getInstantiatedFromMemberFunction()) {
4385  const FunctionDecl *Definition;
4386  if (FD->hasBody(Definition))
4387  return Definition->isOutOfLine();
4388  }
4389 
4390  // If this function was instantiated from a function template,
4391  // check whether that function template was defined out-of-line.
4392  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl = getPrimaryTemplate()) {
4393  const FunctionDecl *Definition;
4394  if (FunTmpl->getTemplatedDecl()->hasBody(Definition))
4395  return Definition->isOutOfLine();
4396  }
4397 
4398  return false;
4399 }
4400 
4401 SourceRange FunctionDecl::getSourceRange() const {
4402  return SourceRange(getOuterLocStart(), EndRangeLoc);
4403 }
4404 
4405 unsigned FunctionDecl::getMemoryFunctionKind() const {
4406  IdentifierInfo *FnInfo = getIdentifier();
4407 
4408  if (!FnInfo)
4409  return 0;
4410 
4411  // Builtin handling.
4412  switch (getBuiltinID()) {
4413  case Builtin::BI__builtin_memset:
4414  case Builtin::BI__builtin___memset_chk:
4415  case Builtin::BImemset:
4416  return Builtin::BImemset;
4417 
4418  case Builtin::BI__builtin_memcpy:
4419  case Builtin::BI__builtin___memcpy_chk:
4420  case Builtin::BImemcpy:
4421  return Builtin::BImemcpy;
4422 
4423  case Builtin::BI__builtin_mempcpy:
4424  case Builtin::BI__builtin___mempcpy_chk:
4425  case Builtin::BImempcpy:
4426  return Builtin::BImempcpy;
4427 
4428  case Builtin::BI__builtin_memmove:
4429  case Builtin::BI__builtin___memmove_chk:
4430  case Builtin::BImemmove:
4431  return Builtin::BImemmove;
4432 
4433  case Builtin::BIstrlcpy:
4434  case Builtin::BI__builtin___strlcpy_chk:
4435  return Builtin::BIstrlcpy;
4436 
4437  case Builtin::BIstrlcat:
4438  case Builtin::BI__builtin___strlcat_chk:
4439  return Builtin::BIstrlcat;
4440 
4441  case Builtin::BI__builtin_memcmp:
4442  case Builtin::BImemcmp:
4443  return Builtin::BImemcmp;
4444 
4445  case Builtin::BI__builtin_bcmp:
4446  case Builtin::BIbcmp:
4447  return Builtin::BIbcmp;
4448 
4449  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strncpy:
4450  case Builtin::BI__builtin___strncpy_chk:
4451  case Builtin::BIstrncpy:
4452  return Builtin::BIstrncpy;
4453 
4454  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strncmp:
4455  case Builtin::BIstrncmp:
4456  return Builtin::BIstrncmp;
4457 
4458  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strncasecmp:
4459  case Builtin::BIstrncasecmp:
4460  return Builtin::BIstrncasecmp;
4461 
4462  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strncat:
4463  case Builtin::BI__builtin___strncat_chk:
4464  case Builtin::BIstrncat:
4465  return Builtin::BIstrncat;
4466 
4467  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strndup:
4468  case Builtin::BIstrndup:
4469  return Builtin::BIstrndup;
4470 
4471  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strlen:
4472  case Builtin::BIstrlen:
4473  return Builtin::BIstrlen;
4474 
4475  case Builtin::BI__builtin_bzero:
4476  case Builtin::BIbzero:
4477  return Builtin::BIbzero;
4478 
4479  case Builtin::BI__builtin_bcopy:
4480  case Builtin::BIbcopy:
4481  return Builtin::BIbcopy;
4482 
4483  case Builtin::BIfree:
4484  return Builtin::BIfree;
4485 
4486  default:
4487  if (isExternC()) {
4488  if (FnInfo->isStr("memset"))
4489  return Builtin::BImemset;
4490  if (FnInfo->isStr("memcpy"))
4491  return Builtin::BImemcpy;
4492  if (FnInfo->isStr("mempcpy"))
4493  return Builtin::BImempcpy;
4494  if (FnInfo->isStr("memmove"))
4495  return Builtin::BImemmove;
4496  if (FnInfo->isStr("memcmp"))
4497  return Builtin::BImemcmp;
4498  if (FnInfo->isStr("bcmp"))
4499  return Builtin::BIbcmp;
4500  if (FnInfo->isStr("strncpy"))
4501  return Builtin::BIstrncpy;
4502  if (FnInfo->isStr("strncmp"))
4503  return Builtin::BIstrncmp;
4504  if (FnInfo->isStr("strncasecmp"))
4505  return Builtin::BIstrncasecmp;
4506  if (FnInfo->isStr("strncat"))
4507  return Builtin::BIstrncat;
4508  if (FnInfo->isStr("strndup"))
4509  return Builtin::BIstrndup;
4510  if (FnInfo->isStr("strlen"))
4511  return Builtin::BIstrlen;
4512  if (FnInfo->isStr("bzero"))
4513  return Builtin::BIbzero;
4514  if (FnInfo->isStr("bcopy"))
4515  return Builtin::BIbcopy;
4516  } else if (isInStdNamespace()) {
4517  if (FnInfo->isStr("free"))
4518  return Builtin::BIfree;
4519  }
4520  break;
4521  }
4522  return 0;
4523 }

4526  assert(hasODRHash());
4527  return ODRHash;
4528 }
4529 
4530 unsigned FunctionDecl::getODRHash() {
4531  if (hasODRHash())
4532  return ODRHash;
4533 
4534  if (auto *FT = getInstantiatedFromMemberFunction()) {
4535  setHasODRHash(true);
4536  ODRHash = FT->getODRHash();
4537  return ODRHash;
4538  }
4539 
4540  class ODRHash Hash;
4541  Hash.AddFunctionDecl(this);
4542  setHasODRHash(true);
4543  ODRHash = Hash.CalculateHash();
4544  return ODRHash;
4545 }

4605  getBitWidthValue(Ctx) == 0;

4607 
4608 bool FieldDecl::isZeroSize(const ASTContext &Ctx) const {
4609  if (isZeroLengthBitField(Ctx))
4610  return true;
4611 
4612  // C++2a [intro.object]p7:
4613  // An object has nonzero size if it
4614  // -- is not a potentially-overlapping subobject, or
4615  if (!hasAttr<NoUniqueAddressAttr>())
4616  return false;
4617 
4618  // -- is not of class type, or
4619  const auto *RT = getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
4620  if (!RT)
4621  return false;
4622  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl()->getDefinition();
4623  if (!RD) {
4624  assert(isInvalidDecl() && "valid field has incomplete type");
4625  return false;
4626  }
4627 
4628  // -- [has] virtual member functions or virtual base classes, or
4629  // -- has subobjects of nonzero size or bit-fields of nonzero length
4630  const auto *CXXRD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD);
4631  if (!CXXRD->isEmpty())
4632  return false;
4633 
4634  // Otherwise, [...] the circumstances under which the object has zero size
4635  // are implementation-defined.
4636  if (!Ctx.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft())
4637  return true;
4638 
4639  // MS ABI: has nonzero size if it is a class type with class type fields,
4640  // whether or not they have nonzero size
4641  return !llvm::any_of(CXXRD->fields(), [](const FieldDecl *Field) {
4642  return Field->getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
4643  });
4644 }
4645 
4646 bool FieldDecl::isPotentiallyOverlapping() const {
4647  return hasAttr<NoUniqueAddressAttr>() && getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4648 }
4649 
4650 unsigned FieldDecl::getFieldIndex() const {
4651  const FieldDecl *Canonical = getCanonicalDecl();
4652  if (Canonical != this)
4653  return Canonical->getFieldIndex();
4654 
4655  if (CachedFieldIndex) return CachedFieldIndex - 1;
4656 
4657  unsigned Index = 0;
4658  const RecordDecl *RD = getParent()->getDefinition();
4659  assert(RD && "requested index for field of struct with no definition");
4660 
4661  for (auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
4662  Field->getCanonicalDecl()->CachedFieldIndex = Index + 1;
4663  assert(Field->getCanonicalDecl()->CachedFieldIndex == Index + 1 &&
4664  "overflow in field numbering");
4665  ++Index;
4666  }
4667 
4668  assert(CachedFieldIndex && "failed to find field in parent");
4669  return CachedFieldIndex - 1;
4670 }
4671 
4672 SourceRange FieldDecl::getSourceRange() const {
4673  const Expr *FinalExpr = getInClassInitializer();
4674  if (!FinalExpr)
4675  FinalExpr = getBitWidth();
4676  if (FinalExpr)
4677  return SourceRange(getInnerLocStart(), FinalExpr->getEndLoc());
4678  return DeclaratorDecl::getSourceRange();
4679 }

4681 void FieldDecl::setCapturedVLAType(const VariableArrayType *VLAType) {
4682  assert((getParent()->isLambda() || getParent()->isCapturedRecord()) &&
4683  "capturing type in non-lambda or captured record.");
4684  assert(StorageKind == ISK_NoInit && !BitField &&
4685  "bit-field or field with default member initializer cannot capture "
4686  "VLA type");
4687  StorageKind = ISK_CapturedVLAType;

4743 void TagDecl::startDefinition() {
4744  setBeingDefined(true);
4745 
4746  if (auto *D = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(this)) {
4747  struct CXXRecordDecl::DefinitionData *Data =
4748  new (getASTContext()) struct CXXRecordDecl::DefinitionData(D);
4749  for (auto *I : redecls())
4750  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(I)->DefinitionData = Data;
4751  }
4752 }
4753 
4754 void TagDecl::completeDefinition() {
4755  assert((!isa<CXXRecordDecl>(this) ||
4756  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(this)->hasDefinition()) &&
4757  "definition completed but not started");
4758 
4759  setCompleteDefinition(true);
4760  setBeingDefined(false);
4761 
4762  if (ASTMutationListener *L = getASTMutationListener())
4763  L->CompletedTagDefinition(this);
4764 }
4765 
4766 TagDecl *TagDecl::getDefinition() const {
4767  if (isCompleteDefinition())
4768  return const_cast<TagDecl *>(this);
4769 
4770  // If it's possible for us to have an out-of-date definition, check now.
4771  if (mayHaveOutOfDateDef()) {
4772  if (IdentifierInfo *II = getIdentifier()) {
4773  if (II->isOutOfDate()) {
4774  updateOutOfDate(*II);
4775  }
4776  }
4777  }
4778 
4779  if (const auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(this))
4780  return CXXRD->getDefinition();
4781 
4782  for (auto *R : redecls())
4783  if (R->isCompleteDefinition())
4784  return R;
4785 
4786  return nullptr;
4787 }

4789 void TagDecl::setQualifierInfo(NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc) {
4790  if (QualifierLoc) {
4791  // Make sure the extended qualifier info is allocated.
4792  if (!hasExtInfo())
4793  TypedefNameDeclOrQualifier = new (getASTContext()) ExtInfo;
4794  // Set qualifier info.
4795  getExtInfo()->QualifierLoc = QualifierLoc;
4796  } else {
4797  // Here Qualifier == 0, i.e., we are removing the qualifier (if any).
4798  if (hasExtInfo()) {
4799  if (getExtInfo()->NumTemplParamLists == 0) {
4800  getASTContext().Deallocate(getExtInfo());
4801  TypedefNameDeclOrQualifier = (TypedefNameDecl *)nullptr;
4802  }
4803  else
4804  getExtInfo()->QualifierLoc = QualifierLoc;
4805  }
4806  }
4807 }
4808 
4809 void TagDecl::printName(raw_ostream &OS, const PrintingPolicy &Policy) const {
4810  DeclarationName Name = getDeclName();
4811  // If the name is supposed to have an identifier but does not have one, then
4812  // the tag is anonymous and we should print it differently.
4813  if (Name.isIdentifier() && !Name.getAsIdentifierInfo()) {
4814  // If the caller wanted to print a qualified name, they've already printed
4815  // the scope. And if the caller doesn't want that, the scope information
4816  // is already printed as part of the type.
4817  PrintingPolicy Copy(Policy);
4818  Copy.SuppressScope = true;
4819  getASTContext().getTagDeclType(this).print(OS, Copy);
4820  return;
4821  }
4822  // Otherwise, do the normal printing.
4823  Name.print(OS, Policy);
4824 }

4828  assert(!TPLists.empty());
4829  // Make sure the extended decl info is allocated.
4830  if (!hasExtInfo())
4831  // Allocate external info struct.
4832  TypedefNameDeclOrQualifier = new (getASTContext()) ExtInfo;
4833  // Set the template parameter lists info.
4834  getExtInfo()->setTemplateParameterListsInfo(Context, TPLists);
4835 }

4929 EnumDecl *EnumDecl::getTemplateInstantiationPattern() const {
4930  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo = getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
4931  if (isTemplateInstantiation(MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind())) {
4932  EnumDecl *ED = getInstantiatedFromMemberEnum();
4933  while (auto *NewED = ED->getInstantiatedFromMemberEnum())
4934  ED = NewED;
4935  return getDefinitionOrSelf(ED);
4936  }
4937  }
4938 
4939  assert(!isTemplateInstantiation(getTemplateSpecializationKind()) &&
4940  "couldn't find pattern for enum instantiation");
4941  return nullptr;
4942 }
4943 
4944 EnumDecl *EnumDecl::getInstantiatedFromMemberEnum() const {
4945  if (SpecializationInfo)
4946  return cast<EnumDecl>(SpecializationInfo->getInstantiatedFrom());
4947 
4948  return nullptr;
4949 }

4957 unsigned EnumDecl::getODRHash() {
4958  if (hasODRHash())
4959  return ODRHash;
4960 
4961  class ODRHash Hash;
4962  Hash.AddEnumDecl(this);
4963  setHasODRHash(true);
4964  ODRHash = Hash.CalculateHash();
4965  return ODRHash;
4966 }
4967 
4968 SourceRange EnumDecl::getSourceRange() const {
4969  auto Res = TagDecl::getSourceRange();
4970  // Set end-point to enum-base, e.g. enum foo : ^bar
4971  if (auto *TSI = getIntegerTypeSourceInfo()) {
4972  // TagDecl doesn't know about the enum base.
4973  if (!getBraceRange().getEnd().isValid())
4974  Res.setEnd(TSI->getTypeLoc().getEndLoc());
4975  }
4976  return Res;
4977 }
4978 
4979 void EnumDecl::getValueRange(llvm::APInt &Max, llvm::APInt &Min) const {
4980  unsigned Bitwidth = getASTContext().getIntWidth(getIntegerType());
4981  unsigned NumNegativeBits = getNumNegativeBits();
4982  unsigned NumPositiveBits = getNumPositiveBits();
4983 
4984  if (NumNegativeBits) {
4985  unsigned NumBits = std::max(NumNegativeBits, NumPositiveBits + 1);
4986  Max = llvm::APInt(Bitwidth, 1) << (NumBits - 1);
4987  Min = -Max;
4988  } else {
4989  Max = llvm::APInt(Bitwidth, 1) << NumPositiveBits;
4990  Min = llvm::APInt::getZero(Bitwidth);
4991  }
4992 }
