5059 bool RecordDecl::isOrContainsUnion() const {
5060  if (isUnion())
5061  return true;
5062 
5063  if (const RecordDecl *Def = getDefinition()) {
5064  for (const FieldDecl *FD : Def->fields()) {
5065  const RecordType *RT = FD->getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
5066  if (RT && RT->getDecl()->isOrContainsUnion())
5067  return true;
5068  }
5069  }
5070 
5071  return false;
5072 }
5073 
5074 RecordDecl::field_iterator RecordDecl::field_begin() const {
5075  if (hasExternalLexicalStorage() && !hasLoadedFieldsFromExternalStorage())
5076  LoadFieldsFromExternalStorage();
5077  // This is necessary for correctness for C++ with modules.
5078  // FIXME: Come up with a test case that breaks without definition.
5079  if (RecordDecl *D = getDefinition(); D && D != this)
5080  return D->field_begin();
5081  return field_iterator(decl_iterator(FirstDecl));
5082 }
5083 
5084 /// completeDefinition - Notes that the definition of this type is now
5085 /// complete.
5086 void RecordDecl::completeDefinition() {
5087  assert(!isCompleteDefinition() && "Cannot redefine record!");
5088  TagDecl::completeDefinition();
5089 
5090  ASTContext &Ctx = getASTContext();
5091 
5092  // Layouts are dumped when computed, so if we are dumping for all complete
5093  // types, we need to force usage to get types that wouldn't be used elsewhere.
5094  //
5095  // If the type is dependent, then we can't compute its layout because there
5096  // is no way for us to know the size or alignment of a dependent type. Also
5097  // ignore declarations marked as invalid since 'getASTRecordLayout()' asserts
5098  // on that.
5099  if (Ctx.getLangOpts().DumpRecordLayoutsComplete && !isDependentType() &&
5100  !isInvalidDecl())
5101  (void)Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(this);
5102 }
5103 
5104 /// isMsStruct - Get whether or not this record uses ms_struct layout.
5105 /// This which can be turned on with an attribute, pragma, or the
5106 /// -mms-bitfields command-line option.
5107 bool RecordDecl::isMsStruct(const ASTContext &C) const {
5108  return hasAttr<MSStructAttr>() || C.getLangOpts().MSBitfields == 1;
5109 }
5110 
5111 void RecordDecl::reorderDecls(const SmallVectorImpl<Decl *> &Decls) {
5112  std::tie(FirstDecl, LastDecl) = DeclContext::BuildDeclChain(Decls, false);
5113  LastDecl->NextInContextAndBits.setPointer(nullptr);
5114  setIsRandomized(true);
5115 }
5116 
5117 void RecordDecl::LoadFieldsFromExternalStorage() const {
5118  ExternalASTSource *Source = getASTContext().getExternalSource();
5119  assert(hasExternalLexicalStorage() && Source && "No external storage?");
5120 
5121  // Notify that we have a RecordDecl doing some initialization.
5122  ExternalASTSource::Deserializing TheFields(Source);
5123 
5124  SmallVector<Decl*, 64> Decls;
5125  setHasLoadedFieldsFromExternalStorage(true);
5126  Source->FindExternalLexicalDecls(this, [](Decl::Kind K) {
5127  return FieldDecl::classofKind(K) || IndirectFieldDecl::classofKind(K);
5128  }, Decls);
5129 
5130 #ifndef NDEBUG
5131  // Check that all decls we got were FieldDecls.
5132  for (unsigned i=0, e=Decls.size(); i != e; ++i)
5133  assert(isa<FieldDecl>(Decls[i]) || isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(Decls[i]));
5134 #endif
5135 
5136  if (Decls.empty())
5137  return;
5138 
5139  auto [ExternalFirst, ExternalLast] =
5140  BuildDeclChain(Decls,
5141  /*FieldsAlreadyLoaded=*/false);
5142  ExternalLast->NextInContextAndBits.setPointer(FirstDecl);
5143  FirstDecl = ExternalFirst;
5144  if (!LastDecl)
5145  LastDecl = ExternalLast;
5146 }
5147 
5148 bool RecordDecl::mayInsertExtraPadding(bool EmitRemark) const {
5149  ASTContext &Context = getASTContext();
5150  const SanitizerMask EnabledAsanMask = Context.getLangOpts().Sanitize.Mask &
5151  (SanitizerKind::Address | SanitizerKind::KernelAddress);
5152  if (!EnabledAsanMask || !Context.getLangOpts().SanitizeAddressFieldPadding)
5153  return false;
5154  const auto &NoSanitizeList = Context.getNoSanitizeList();
5155  const auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(this);
5156  // We may be able to relax some of these requirements.
5157  int ReasonToReject = -1;
5158  if (!CXXRD || CXXRD->isExternCContext())
5159  ReasonToReject = 0; // is not C++.
5160  else if (CXXRD->hasAttr<PackedAttr>())
5161  ReasonToReject = 1; // is packed.
5162  else if (CXXRD->isUnion())
5163  ReasonToReject = 2; // is a union.
5164  else if (CXXRD->isTriviallyCopyable())
5165  ReasonToReject = 3; // is trivially copyable.
5166  else if (CXXRD->hasTrivialDestructor())
5167  ReasonToReject = 4; // has trivial destructor.
5168  else if (CXXRD->isStandardLayout())
5169  ReasonToReject = 5; // is standard layout.
5170  else if (NoSanitizeList.containsLocation(EnabledAsanMask, getLocation(),
5171  "field-padding"))
5172  ReasonToReject = 6; // is in an excluded file.
5173  else if (NoSanitizeList.containsType(
5174  EnabledAsanMask, getQualifiedNameAsString(), "field-padding"))
5175  ReasonToReject = 7; // The type is excluded.
5176 
5177  if (EmitRemark) {
5178  if (ReasonToReject >= 0)
5179  Context.getDiagnostics().Report(
5180  getLocation(),
5181  diag::remark_sanitize_address_insert_extra_padding_rejected)
5182  << getQualifiedNameAsString() << ReasonToReject;
5183  else
5184  Context.getDiagnostics().Report(
5185  getLocation(),
5186  diag::remark_sanitize_address_insert_extra_padding_accepted)
5187  << getQualifiedNameAsString();
5188  }
5189  return ReasonToReject < 0;
5190 }
5191 
5192 const FieldDecl *RecordDecl::findFirstNamedDataMember() const {
5193  for (const auto *I : fields()) {
5194  if (I->getIdentifier())
5195  return I;
5196 
5197  if (const auto *RT = I->getType()->getAs<RecordType>())
5198  if (const FieldDecl *NamedDataMember =
5199  RT->getDecl()->findFirstNamedDataMember())
5200  return NamedDataMember;
5201  }
5202 
5203  // We didn't find a named data member.
5204  return nullptr;
5205 }
5206 
5207 unsigned RecordDecl::getODRHash() {
5208  if (hasODRHash())
5209  return RecordDeclBits.ODRHash;
5210 
5211  // Only calculate hash on first call of getODRHash per record.
5212  ODRHash Hash;
5213  Hash.AddRecordDecl(this);
5214  // For RecordDecl the ODRHash is stored in the remaining 26
5215  // bit of RecordDeclBits, adjust the hash to accomodate.
5216  setODRHash(Hash.CalculateHash() >> 6);
5217  return RecordDeclBits.ODRHash;
5218 }

5517 TagDecl *TypedefNameDecl::getAnonDeclWithTypedefName(bool AnyRedecl) const {
5518  if (auto *TT = getTypeSourceInfo()->getType()->getAs<TagType>()) {
5519  auto *OwningTypedef = TT->getDecl()->getTypedefNameForAnonDecl();
5520  auto *ThisTypedef = this;
5521  if (AnyRedecl && OwningTypedef) {
5522  OwningTypedef = OwningTypedef->getCanonicalDecl();
5523  ThisTypedef = ThisTypedef->getCanonicalDecl();
5524  }
5525  if (OwningTypedef == ThisTypedef)
5526  return TT->getDecl();
5527  }
5528 
5529  return nullptr;
5530 }
5531 
5532 bool TypedefNameDecl::isTransparentTagSlow() const {
5533  auto determineIsTransparent = [&]() {
5534  if (auto *TT = getUnderlyingType()->getAs<TagType>()) {
5535  if (auto *TD = TT->getDecl()) {
5536  if (TD->getName() != getName())
5537  return false;
5538  SourceLocation TTLoc = getLocation();
5539  SourceLocation TDLoc = TD->getLocation();
5540  if (!TTLoc.isMacroID() || !TDLoc.isMacroID())
5541  return false;
5542  SourceManager &SM = getASTContext().getSourceManager();
5543  return SM.getSpellingLoc(TTLoc) == SM.getSpellingLoc(TDLoc);
5544  }
5545  }
5546  return false;
5547  };
5548 
5549  bool isTransparent = determineIsTransparent();
5550  MaybeModedTInfo.setInt((isTransparent << 1) | 1);
5551  return isTransparent;
5552 }

5679 /// Retrieve the number of module identifiers needed to name the given
5680 /// module.
5681 static unsigned getNumModuleIdentifiers(Module *Mod) {
5682  unsigned Result = 1;
5683  while (Mod->Parent) {
5684  Mod = Mod->Parent;
5685  ++Result;
5686  }
5687  return Result;
5688 }

5690 ImportDecl::ImportDecl(DeclContext *DC, SourceLocation StartLoc,
5691  Module *Imported,
5692  ArrayRef<SourceLocation> IdentifierLocs)
5693  : Decl(Import, DC, StartLoc), ImportedModule(Imported),
5694  NextLocalImportAndComplete(nullptr, true) {
5695  assert(getNumModuleIdentifiers(Imported) == IdentifierLocs.size());
5696  auto *StoredLocs = getTrailingObjects<SourceLocation>();
5697  std::uninitialized_copy(IdentifierLocs.begin(), IdentifierLocs.end(),
5698  StoredLocs);
5699 }
